quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,11,"Say thou: verily I am commanded to worship Allah, making for Him religion exclusive"
  39,12,"And I am commanded this, in order I may be the first Of those who submit"
  39,13,"Say thou: verily fear, if I disobeyed my Lord, torment of a Day mighty"
  39,14,"Say thou: it is Allah I worship, making for Him my religion exclusive"
  39,15,"So worship whatsoever ye will, besidev him. Say thou: verily the losers are those who shall have lost themselves and their household\" on the Day of judgment LO! that will be a loss manifest"
  39,16,For them! above them shall be coverings of Fire and beneath them coverings. Therewith Allah affrighteth His bondmen. O My bondmen! wherefore fear Me
  39,17,"And those who avoid the devils lest they should worship them and turn Unto Allah in penitence, for them are glad tidings. Wherefore give thou glad tidings Unto My bondmen"
  39,18,"Who hearken Unto the word and follow that which is the exceLlent there of. These are they whom Allah hath guided, and those are men of understanding"
  39,19,Is he then on whom is justified the decree of torment - wilt thou rescue him who is in the Fire
  39,20,"But those whofear their Lord, for them are lofty chambers with lofty chambers above them, built whereunder rivers flow: the promise of Allah, and Allah faileth not the appointment"
  39,21,"Beholdest thou not that Allah sendeth down water from the heaven, and causeth it to enter springs in the earth, and thereafter produceth thereby corn various coloured. Thereafter it wirhereth, and thou beholdest it turn yellow; then He maketh it chaff. Verily herein is an admonition for men of understanding"